Hi there! These videos strictly follow the syllabus for Paper 0610.

Hi, veins have a larger space inside (lumen) than arteries because veins carry blood back to the heart, and the larger space helps accommodate the slower and less pressurized flow of blood. Arteries, on the other hand, have a smaller lumen to maintain the higher pressure needed to pump oxygenated blood away from the heart.
